                <h1>Founders of the United Nations: Pioneers of Global Cooperation</h1>
                <p>The United Nations was founded in 1945, following the devastation of World War II, to promote peace and cooperation among nations. Key figures like Franklin D. Roosevelt, Winston Churchill, and others emphasized collective security and human rights. The UN's establishment marked a commitment to prevent future conflicts and foster global partnership.</p>
